development/architecture.title: Architecture Guide
development/architecture.description: This guide provides a comprehensive overview of the TrainLoop Evals architecture, including system design, component interactions, and data flow patterns.

development/building-from-source.title: Building from Source
development/building-from-source.description: This guide covers building TrainLoop Evals from source code, including all components and their dependencies.

development/code-style.title: Code Style Guide
development/code-style.description: This guide defines the coding standards and conventions used across the TrainLoop Evals project. Following these guidelines ensures consistency, readability, and maintainability.

development/contributing.title: Contributing Guide
development/contributing.description: Welcome to the TrainLoop Evals project! We're excited to have you contribute to our comprehensive LLM evaluation framework. This guide will help you get started with contributing to the project.

development/index.title: Development Guide
development/index.description: This section contains information for developers who want to contribute to TrainLoop Evals or extend its functionality. Whether you're fixing bugs, adding features, or building custom integrations, this guide will help you get started.

development/local-development.title: Local Development
development/local-development.description: This guide walks you through setting up a complete development environment for TrainLoop Evals on your local machine.

development/pull-request-process.title: Pull Request Process
development/pull-request-process.description: This guide covers the complete pull request workflow for contributing to TrainLoop Evals, from preparation to merge.

development/release-process.title: Release Process
development/release-process.description: This document describes the TrainLoop Evals release process, including version bumping, changelog management, and publication workflows.

development/sdk-testing.title: SDK Testing Guide
development/sdk-testing.description: This document describes how to run tests for both Python and TypeScript SDKs in the TrainLoop Evals ecosystem.

development/testing.title: Testing Guide
development/testing.description: This guide covers the comprehensive testing framework used in TrainLoop Evals, including test categories, execution methods, and best practices.

explanation/index.title: Understanding TrainLoop Evals
explanation/index.description: This section provides in-depth explanations of TrainLoop Evals concepts, architecture, and design decisions. These guides help you understand the "why" behind TrainLoop Evals.

getting-started/installation.title: Installation
getting-started/installation.description: Get started with TrainLoop Evals by installing the CLI tool and SDKs. This guide covers all installation methods and platform-specific requirements.

getting-started/quick-start.title: Quick Start Guide
getting-started/quick-start.description: Get up and running with TrainLoop Evals in under 5 minutes. This guide walks you through setting up your first evaluation project, collecting LLM data, and running your first evaluations.

guides/index.title: TrainLoop Evals Guides
guides/index.description: This section contains practical guides for using TrainLoop Evals effectively. Each guide focuses on accomplishing specific tasks and solving common use cases.

intro.title: Introduction to TrainLoop Evals
intro.description: Welcome to TrainLoop Evals, a comprehensive framework for automating the collection and evaluation of Large Language Model (LLM) outputs. TrainLoop Evals simplifies the process of testing and improving your AI applications with a focus on developer experience and reliability.

reference/benchmark-schema.title: Benchmark Data Schema
reference/benchmark-schema.description: The benchmark feature enables comparing evaluation results across multiple LLM providers. This document describes the data schema and JSONL output format for benchmark runs.

reference/cli/overview.title: CLI Overview
reference/cli/overview.description: The TrainLoop CLI provides four main commands for managing your evaluation workflow. This page provides a comprehensive reference for all CLI commands and options.

reference/index.title: Reference
reference/index.description: This section contains detailed API documentation and reference materials for TrainLoop Evals.
